<subSubSection pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="104.[151,1436,362,675]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,398,423]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Remarks.</emphasis>
We prefer not to describe the single specimen of this possible new species, because the taxonomy of the genus is very confused, particulartly in the group to which it could be referable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="104.[151,1436,362,675]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
This species is similar to 
<emphasis box="[493,625,471,494]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Z. coccinea</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1801) from Western and central Africa, and to 
<emphasis box="[1305,1436,470,494]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Z. suaveola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Peringuey" box="[158,350,506,531]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" refString="Peringuey, L. (1899) Fifth contribution to the South African Coleopterous Fauna. Annals of the South African Museum, 1, 240 - 329." type="journal article" year="1899">Péringuey, 1899</bibRefCitation>
) from southern Africa, which was synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peringuey" box="[981,1183,506,531]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" refString="Peringuey, L. (1909) Descriptive catalogue of the Coleoptera of South Africa Family Meloidae. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Africa, 1, 165 - 297, 4 pls." type="journal article" year="1909">Péringuey (1909)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<emphasis box="[1231,1366,507,530]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Z. coccinea</emphasis>
. This synonymy needs confirmation after the revision of the genus also because most southern Africa specimens of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Z. coccinea</emphasis>
slightly differ from those from the Guinean Gulf (type locality).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="104.[151,1436,362,675]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
The Kavango’ specimen differs from both 
<emphasis box="[679,808,615,638]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Z. coccinea</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[863,993,614,638]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Z. suaveola</emphasis>
by its shorter frontal region, eyes more bulged, ventral setae sparser.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
